  "prompt": "Is there any app like Shazam to get the chord tabs when hearing a song?",
  "response": "While there isn't an exact replica of Shazam for chord tabs, there are several apps and websites that can help you identify chords or get chord information:\n\n1. Chord Genie\n- Tries to detect chords from audio\n- Available on mobile platforms\n\n2. Guitar Tuna\n- Has chord detection features\n- Also includes tuner and other guitar-related tools\n\n3. Chord ai\n- Uses AI to analyze audio and generate chord progressions\n- Available on iOS and Android\n\n4. Capo Touch\n- Analyzes audio and provides chord detection\n- Primarily for Mac and iOS\n\n5. Chord detector websites:\n- Chordify\n- Chord Detect\n\n6. Music recognition apps with chord info:\n- Ultimate Guitar\n- Songsterr\n- Guitar Pro\n\nWhile these options can help, they might not be as instantaneous or accurate as Shazam is for song identification. Some require manual input or have limitations.\n\nFor the most accurate results, you might need to combine multiple tools or methods, like listening carefully and cross-referencing different sources.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these options?",
